        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Just an FYI:</P><P>I submitted the below list to VI as my recommended list of spells and AA's for pop.  Just wanted to know what the rest of u thought about them.</P><P>~~~~~~~~~</P><P>My requests are primarily based from 3 themes.  Firstly, the necromancer is to the dot, that the wizard is to the DD.  Provide us both spell enhancements and AA enhancements that will parallel the improvements made for the wizard class in the SoL expansion.</P><P>Secondly, there is a real need for improving and enhancing our abilities within a fast xp group.  I've recommend some group oriented spells that i feel would sufficiently improve our demand when LFG in the popular xp zones of EQ.</P><P>Thirdly, necromancers are the masters of the undead.  Provide us with a bane dd, and a bane undead dot to further our standing in this arena.  Our current speciality undead dd's are quite weak in comparison to the standard DD's of the wizard, druid and mage classes.</P><P>Spells:<BR>1) Splurt Upgrade: Lvl 59-60, Dmg 2400, duration 90 seconds, mana 350.  Resist check = same as lvl 51 splurt spell.</P><P>2) Poison DD Upgrade: Lvl 57, dmg 850, mana 350, no residual affect (aka stuns, illusions, etc..).  This spell should be subject to partials resists.</P><P>3) Screaming terror upgrade I: Lvl 49, Lvl limit - same as ST (lvl 54), duration 42 seconds, 6 second recast, 3 second cast time, mana 100. </P><P>4) Screaming terror upgrade II: Lvl 58-59, lvl limit - same as GoK (chanter spell), duration 24 seconds, 6 second recast, 3 second cast time, mana 120.</P><P>5) Cold Dot I: lvl 51, dmg 1000, duration 90 seconds, mana 275mana. Resists should be near lure - similar to our blood dot line.</P><P>6) Cold Dot II: Lvl 59-60, dmg 1800, duration 90 seconds, mana 400.  Resists should be near lure - similar to our blood dot line.</P><P>7) Undead Bane DD: Lvl 60, dmg 1200, mana 300, regent = peridot.  Like dragon/giant bane spells, this should be unresistable.</P><P>8) Undead Bane Dot: Lvl 60, dmg 2800, mana 500, duration = 60seconds, regent = peridot.  Like dragon/giant bane spells, this should be unresistable.</P><P>AA's<BR>1) Dot fury<BR>Type: Arch<BR>Increments: 2pts for lvl 1, 4pts for lvl 2, 6 pts for lvl 3.<BR>Effect: Increase dot damage by 33, 66 and 100 percent for the dot's original duration. The probability for a crit should be 2, 4 and 7 percent for each respective fury level.</P><P>2) Dot fury mastery<BR>Type: Class<BR>Increments: 3pts for lvl 1, 6 for lvl 2, 9 for lvl 3.  <BR>Effect: Same crit probabilities as casting fury mastery</P><P>3) Innate Feign<BR>Type: Class<BR>Increment: 1 lvl 9 pts<BR>Effect: 1 second cast FD, with a 15 second reuse timer.</P><P>4) Improved Lich<BR>Type: Class<BR>Increment: 1 lvl, 9pts<BR>Effect: Convert 60mana, into 40hps, duration 36mins, reuse, 10mins<BR>***edit - meant to write 60hps into 40mana ****</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" target="_blank">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><br><BR><a href="http://www.veilofsilence.org" target="_blank">Veil of Silence</a><br> <BR>Innoruuk Server</P><P>Edited by - Tencor on 07/12/2002  14:49:52</P><P>Edited by - Tencor on 07/12/2002  23:05:08</font></td>

